				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It seems for me that the correct path for the initial setup was &quot;bbantispam/bbantispam.php&quot;. But as it works now, let's don't change anything.
<br />

<br />
I feel sorry for all the frustration. The graphical installer is under development, but it isn't going to appear soon.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Well mine is still working, it's just not consistent where it shows up? We've tested it several times and it either comes up during registration or before you post something. Both options are fine with me.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
ATC shows up the first time when a visitor tries to submit something. If he starts with posting a message, ATC appears on posting, if he starts with registering, ATC comes up during registration. As long as the test is successfully passed, the visitor isn't annoyed anymore.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Any other good MODS you could recommend?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
You don't need anything else.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Anyone know how to target before a post only or during registration only?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
It's possible if you remove the call to bbantispam from &quot;extensions.inc&quot; and add the call in the right places to &quot;posting.php&quot; or &quot;includes/usercp_register.php&quot;.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
